09/09/2004
LONDON, Britain -- Britain firmly supports the EU accession calendar for Romania and the conclusion of accession negotiations this year, Romanian President Ion Iliescu was told on the first day of his official visit to London Wednesday (8 September). 
After meetings with Prime Minister Tony Blair and Foreign Secretary Jack Straw, Iliescu said they expressed appreciation for Romania's efforts to make up for the "huge delay" since 2000 and ensure EU entry in 2007. 
On Thursday, Iliescu will meet with Home Secretary David Blunkett to discuss the British visa regime as applied to Romania. 
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 09/08/04; Mediafax - 08/09/04)
